whereas.text:
Whereas the National Association of Secondary School Principals (NASSP) and the National
			 Association of Elementary School Principals have designated the week of
			 March 31 through April 4, 2014, as National Assistant Principals Week;

Whereas an assistant principal, as a member of the school administration, interacts with many
			 sectors of the school community, including support staff, instructional
			 staff, students, and parents;

Whereas the day-to-day logistical operations of schools require assistant principals to monitor and
			 address facility needs, attendance, transportation issues, and scheduling
			 challenges, as well as supervise extra- and co-curricular events;
